    "<li><b>Temperature:</b> Hotter magma is less viscous, flows more easily.</li></ul>",
    [("Shield Volcano","Broad, gently sloping volcano built from fluid basaltic lava flows; relatively gentle eruptions (e.g., Mauna Loa)."),
     ("Composite Volcano","Steep-sided volcano built of alternating lava and ash layers; highly explosive eruptions (e.g., Mt. St. Helens)."),
     ("Viscosity","Resistance to flow; high-silica magma is more viscous and produces more explosive eruptions."),
     ("Pyroclastic Flow","A fast-moving, extremely hot cloud of gas, ash, and rock fragments; the most deadly volcanic hazard."),
     ("Volcanic Explosivity Index (VEI)","Scale from 0-8 measuring eruption size based on volume of ejected material.")],
